x^2+1=0
x\in\mathbb H
i^2=j^2=k^2=ijk=-1
0 \leq p \leq 1
ij = -ji
x^2 + 1 = 0
p \in [0,1]
x = \sqrt p i + \sqrt{1-p} j
x^2 = (\sqrt p i + \sqrt{1-p} j)^2 = pi^2 + (1-p)j^2 + \sqrt{p(1-p)}(ij + ji)
a, b, c
a^2 + b^2 + c^2 = 1
x = ai + bj + ck
 x^2 = (ai + bj + ck)(ai + bj + ck) = -(a^2 + b^2 + c^2) = -1. 
